PHASE 5 — POLISH & SECURITY
Do this before recording the demo video.
===================================================================================

--- Security checklist ---

1. Run test coverage:
   npx hardhat coverage
   Check that enterDungeon, buyItem, swapGameForPXL, stake, harvest have >90%
   branch coverage.

2. Manual edge case testing (on the live appchain):
   - Deposit 0 tokens → should revert
   - Buy more items than listed → should revert
   - Harvest before 100 blocks → should revert
   - List an item you don't own → should revert

3. Verify access control:
   - Only DungeonDrops can mint items on DungeonDrops' AssetCollection
   - Only HarvestField can mint items on HarvestField's AssetCollection
   - Only game contracts can issue badges via AchievementBadge

--- UX checklist (do ALL of these) ---

  [ ] Loading skeletons on Profile Dashboard (it makes many contract calls)
  [ ] Toast notifications for every tx: pending → confirmed (with tx hash) → error
  [ ] Inline form validation: insufficient balance, wrong amount, username too short
  [ ] Loot animation on DungeonDrops: a chest that opens (500ms CSS transition, no libraries)
  [ ] Progress bar on HarvestField: updates every 5 seconds as blocks advance
  [ ] Disable buttons while a transaction is pending (use isPending from useTBA)
  [ ] Show gas cost estimate before confirming expensive operations
  [ ] Mobile-responsive layout on Profile Dashboard, DungeonDrops, and Marketplace


===================================================================================
PHASE 6 — PXL GAS TOKEN MIGRATION
Do this LAST. After the entire demo loop works with standard PXLToken.
===================================================================================

This is where we make PXL the chain's actual gas token. It activates the
core pitch: "players never hold gas tokens."

DO NOT DO THIS until profile → dungeon → marketplace → harvest all work
end-to-end. A broken gas migration kills everything, and there's no easy undo.

Step by step:

1. In deploy.ts, change 'PXLToken' to 'PXLTokenInitia' (around line 23).
   PXLTokenInitia inherits InitiaERC20 which uses MiniEVM precompiles at
   0xF1 and 0xF2. These only exist on the real MiniEVM chain (not Hardhat's
   local network), so unit tests won't work with PXLTokenInitia — that's expected.

2. Redeploy everything:
   npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.ts --network minievm
   npx hardhat run scripts/wire.ts --network minievm
   All contract addresses change because PXL's address changes. deployed-addresses.json
   gets overwritten automatically.

3. Register PXL as the chain's fee denomination:
   Use @initia/initia.js to send a MsgUpdateEvmParams with fee_denom set to
   'evm/<PXLContractAddress>' (WITHOUT the 0x prefix).
   The validator mnemonic is in ~/.weave/config.json under system_keys.validator.mnemonic.

   Example fee_denom: 'evm/5FbDB2315678afecb367f032d93F642f64180aa3'
   (Note: lowercase hex, no 0x. This format is Initia-specific.)

4. Test it: send any transaction and check that gas was charged in PXL,
   not the native chain token. The Gas Settings screen should reflect this.


===================================================================================
PHASE 7 — SUBMISSION PACKAGE
README + submission.json + demo video. This IS the submission.
===================================================================================

--- submission.json ---

Create .initia/submission.json in the repo root. Every field is required:

{
  "project_name": "PixelVault",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/Kumarutkarsh9470/INITIA_Hack",
  "commit_sha": "<40-character hex SHA of your final commit>",
  "rollup_chain_id": "trying",
  "deployed_address": "<PlayerProfile contract address from deployed-addresses.json>",
  "vm": "evm",
  "native_feature": "auto-signing",
  "core_logic_path": "pixelvault/contracts/Marketplace.sol",
  "native_feature_frontend_path": "frontend/src/hooks/useAutoSign.ts",
  "demo_video_url": "<Loom or YouTube link — record AFTER PXL migration>"
}

To get the commit SHA: git rev-parse HEAD


--- README.md ---

The README is judged. Use this exact structure:

  ## Initia Hackathon Submission

  - **Project Name**: PixelVault

  ### Project Overview
  [3 sentences: what it is, what problem it solves, who it's for]

  ### Custom Implementation
  - The TBA identity system: every player gets an NFT wallet that holds
    all their game assets across games.
  - GasPaymaster: players pay gas in any game token — automatic swap
    to PXL behind the scenes.
  - Cross-game economy: game tokens trade on a shared DEX, game ratings
    are driven by real trade volume, CommonRelic items have different
    values per game.

  ### Native Features
  - Auto-signing: session keys scoped to the TBA. Players approve once
    and play without wallet popups.
  - Initia Usernames: .init names resolve throughout the UI.
  - Bridge: one-button bridge from L1 via InterwovenKit.

  ### How to Run Locally
  1. Clone the repo and install: `cd pixelvault && npm install`
  2. Start your appchain: `weave rollup start -d`
  3. Deploy contracts: `npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.ts --network minievm && npx hardhat run scripts/wire.ts --network minievm`
  4. Start frontend: `cd frontend && npm run dev`

  ### Contract Addresses
  [Table of all addresses from deployed-addresses.json]

  ### Market Understanding
  PixelVault targets crypto-native gamers frustrated by wallet interruptions
  and siloed game economies. Existing solutions like Treasure DAO on Arbitrum
  aggregate games but don't solve gas abstraction or portable identity.
  PixelVault's competitive moat is architectural: by making PXL the chain's
  fee token via MsgUpdateEvmParams, gas abstraction happens at the
  infrastructure layer — every game on the platform inherits it automatically.
  This is only possible on Initia.


--- Demo Video Script (aim for 90 seconds) ---

Record this exact sequence. Each step maps to a scoring criterion.
Don't improvise — judges are checking specific things.

 1. Connect wallet → Create profile "AliceGamer" → TBA address appears
    (Shows: appchain works, PlayerProfile NFT, ERC-6551 TBA creation)

 2. View Profile Dashboard — empty tokens, 0 reputation, no items
    (Shows: rich identity UI, contract reads all working)

 3. DEX → Swap 500 PXL for DNGN tokens
    (Shows: AMM works, game token economy)

 4. DungeonDrops → Click "Enter Dungeon" 3 times rapidly, ZERO wallet popups
    → get a Rare Shield drop
    (Shows: AUTO-SIGNING. This is the single most important 10 seconds.)

 5. Gas Settings → Show "3x enterDungeon, paid DNGN, converted to PXL auto"
    (Shows: GasPaymaster, PXL as gas token — the Initia-specific capability)

 6. Profile Dashboard → Badge earned, Rare Shield in inventory, reputation up
    (Shows: items go to TBA, achievement system, reputation scoring)

 7. Marketplace → List the Rare Shield for 200 PXL
    (Shows: marketplace listing flow)

 8. Open a second browser profile as "Bob" → Buy the Rare Shield using HRV tokens
    → Show the DEX auto-swap happening in the background
    (Shows: cross-token payments, DEX integration in marketplace)

 9. Show Bob's profile (shield in inventory) and Alice's profile (195 PXL after fee)
    (Shows: full economy loop, marketplace fee system)

10. HarvestField → Stake HRV → mine blocks → Harvest → item + badge on profile
    (Shows: second game mechanic, complete platform loop)

RECORDING TIP: Use two Chrome profiles (Profile 1 = Alice, Profile 2 = Bob).
Keep both windows open side by side. Switch between them during recording.
Way cleaner than disconnecting/reconnecting wallets mid-video.


